# Bounded type parameters

## Constrain with `extends`

- `<T extends Number>` ‚Äî T is a `Number` or subtype; unlocks `doubleValue()`

```java
public static <T extends Number> double sum(List<T> list) { ... }
Stats.sum(List.of(1, 2, 3));      // ok
// Stats.sum(List.of("a", "b"));  // COMPILE ERROR
```

## Chain bounds with `&`

- `<T extends Number & Comparable<T>>` ‚Äî both a `Number` and self-comparable
